<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="arise-vi">arise <strong><em>vi</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ə'raɪz/    美 /ə'raɪz/  </p>
<p>(arose, arisen) [正式用语]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-occur">1.★ <strong>(问题或困难) 出现；发生；产生(occur)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>What problems may arise when humans are cloned?
克隆人类的时候会发生什么问题？</p><footer>人教⑧ – 2</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A number of high buildings have arisen where there was nothing a year ago but ruins.  
在一年前还是废墟的地方立起了许多高楼大厦。</p><footer>2012 山东</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>起身；起立：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He <strong>arose from</strong> his seat.
他从座位上站了起来。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="arise-from-out-of">arise from / out of</h3>
<p>1.<strong>因…产生；由…引起：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Accidents often arise from / out of carelessness. 
事故往往由粗心引起。</p></div></div>